The Reformation Period (1534-1603) in England created a new reality for Britain, and even the whole world as King Henry VIII (1491-1547) created Protestantism, against the Catholic Church in his quest to produce a male heir.
This story focuses on both the causes and effects of the shift from Catholicism to Protestantism due to King Henry VIII wanting to divorce his wife Katherine of Aragon (1485-1536). The target audience being students, historians, or just someone interested in the impact King Henry VIII had on the socio-political climate of his reign.
